Sentencas: The power output of solid oxide fuel cells using samarium doped ceria electrolyte fabricated by a single-step co-firing process is enhanced by using a surface modification strategy.
Titulo: Surface Modification Allows High Performance for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Fabricated by a Single-step Co-firing Process

Sentencas: This strategy leads to the cell performance improving from 401 mW cm(-2) to 523 mW cm(-2) at 700 degrees C, with an increase of more than 30% been achieved, which is very encouraging considering the large electrolyte thickness (approximate to 500 mu m).
Titulo: Surface Modification Allows High Performance for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Fabricated by a Single-step Co-firing Process

Sentencas: The cell resistance, including both polarization resistance and the ohmic resistance, decreases dramatically by employing the surface modification method.
Titulo: Surface Modification Allows High Performance for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Fabricated by a Single-step Co-firing Process

Sentencas: Those results reveal that the surface modification improves the cathode/electrolyte interfacial contact, which results in a reduced total cell resistance and leads to a better cell performance.
Titulo: Surface Modification Allows High Performance for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Fabricated by a Single-step Co-firing Process
